  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nForge\r\n\r\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\r\n\r\n- [X] Foundry\r\n- [X] Foundryup\r\n\r\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\r\n\r\nforge 0.2.0 (20e7386 2022-08-31T00:07:17.984886151Z)\r\n\r\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\r\n\r\nforge fmt\r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\nLinux\r\n\r\n### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nForge fmt doesn't mind small violations of the line length in multi-line function calls. Here's an example:\r\n```solidity\r\ncontract NotSoPretty {\r\n    function foo() public pure {\r\n        // The line has length 122\r\n        bar(\r\n            111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111, 111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111\r\n        );\r\n        // Extend the line to 123 and it finally breaks\r\n        bar(\r\n            111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111,\r\n            1111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111110\r\n        );\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    function bar(uint256, uint256) private pure {\r\n        return;\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\nThis is after running `forge fmt` with the default line length of 120. The first line is 122 characters which is too long, but extending it to 123 finally triggers breaking the line. ",
